        "accordion_how-it-works": "<p><strong>How to measure your ring size</strong><br/><br/>Wrap a thin strip of paper around the finger you plan to wear the ring on. Mark where the paper overlaps, then measure the length in millimetres. Match to the chart below.<br/><br/><strong>Size chart</strong><br/><br/>Size 8 — 18.3 mm inner diameter (57.5 mm circumference)<br/>Size 9 — 19.1 mm inner diameter (60.0 mm circumference)<br/>Size 10 — 20.0 mm inner diameter (62.8 mm circumference)<br/>Size 11 — 20.8 mm inner diameter (65.3 mm circumference)<br/>Size 12 — 21.6 mm inner diameter (67.9 mm circumference)<br/>Size 13 — 22.4 mm inner diameter (70.4 mm circumference)<br/><br/><strong>Tips</strong><br/>Measure at the end of the day — fingers are slightly larger then.<br/>If you're between sizes, go up one size.<br/>The ring should slide on snugly but come off without effort.<br/>Recommended finger: index or middle finger for best sensor accuracy.</p>",
